<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-04-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-04-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="494" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d494">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Hicks</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-04-06"><hi rend="italic">April 6,
                            1893</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>Mr. Gresham directs Mr. Hicks to enter a protest against the lack of
                        protection to the consulate on the part of the authorities, and in the event
                        of the circumstances being found to have been as reported, to ask that
                        reparation be made for the injury inflicted on the person and property of an
                        American, regret expressed, and offenders promptly prosecuted.</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>